   <refnamediv>
       <refname>delts </refname>
               <refpurpose>differentiates a ts </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>tsout=delts(arg1[,arg2])</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> arg1 </term> =     the order of differenciation (optional, set to 1 if not provided, can be &gt; 0,  =    0 or &lt; 0) or a ts</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> arg2 </term> =     a time series if the first argument was set to the order of differentiation</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> tsout </term> =     the differenciated time series</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Computes x(t)-x(t-n) for a timeseries x. Equivalent, but a little bit quicker than x-lagts(n,x)
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
load(GROCERDIR+'/data\bdhenderic.dat')
y = delts(lm1)
// simple differentiation of the ts lm1
y = delts(1,lm1)
// simple differentiation of the ts lm1
y = delts(4,lm1)
// y=lm1-lm1(-4) (i.e: year on year difference)
y = delts(-3,lm1)
// y=lm1-lm1(+3)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
